Jaap (or Jakob) Kunst  (12 August 1891 in Groningen – 7 December 1960 in Amsterdam) was a Dutch ethnomusicologist, particularly associated with the study of gamelan music of Indonesia.
Kunst was the only child of two musicians, and began to study the violin at only 18 months old.
He earned a degree in law from the University of Groningen in 1917, and pursued a career in banking and law for the next two years.

In 1936 he returned to the Netherlands, and in that same year became the curator of the Royal Tropical Institute in Amsterdam, which developed into one of the most important institutes of its kind in Europe.
